1 local human trafficking task force and any other federal, state or
2 local government or private or nonprofit entity involved in
3 addressing human trafficking;
4 4. Training and mandatory reporting policies and practices
5 utilized in other states, along with a focus on evidence and skills-
6 based training to enhance the identification and reporting of
7 suspected human trafficking;
8 5. Strategic approaches for utilizing and expanding existing
9 statutory and regulatory domestic violence frameworks to enable the
10 State to represent the interests of victims of human trafficking in
11 court proceedings, including a review of the Domestic Violence
12 Prosecution Best Practice Guidelines as adopted by the Committee
13 on Domestic Violence and approved by the Nevada District
14 Attorneys Association;
15 6. Strategies to create regulatory oversight and standards for
16 entities offering services to victims of human trafficking to ensure
17 the quality, safety and effectiveness of the support provided to
18 victims; and
19 7. Any other matters or topics that, in the determination of the
20 Committee, affect the victims or outcomes of human trafficking in
21 this State; and be it further
22 RESOLVED, That the Committee, pursuant to subsection 4 of
23 NRS 218E.330, shall submit a report of the study and any
24 recommendations for legislation to the Director of the Legislative
25 Counsel Bureau for transmittal to the 84th Session of the Nevada
26 Legislature; and be it further
27 RESOLVED, That this resolution becomes effective upon
28 adoption.
